
<h1 id="debugging">Debugging</h1>
<h2 id="browser-dev-tools">Browser Dev Tools</h2>
<p>If you get a generic <em>"Unexpected error."</em> error message or the comments don't load, you can use the browser dev tools to see the actual errors and response from server (make sure the debug mode is enabled).</p>
<p>In Google Chrome, right-click and select <strong>Inspect Element</strong>, or use the keyboard shortcut: <kbd>Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>Shift</kbd>+<kbd>I</kbd> (or <kbd>Cmd</kbd>+<kbd>Opt</kbd>+<kbd>I</kbd> on Mac).</p>
<p>Navigate to the <strong>Console</strong> tab to see potential JavaScript errors and the <strong>Network</strong> tab to see the HTTP requests (make sure <em>Record Network</em> Log is on). </p>
